ue,"content":"Sesame Streusel"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 160°C. Place butter, flour and sugar in mixing bowl then mix <b>40 sec\/speed 4<b>. Tip out onto a silicone baking mat, leaving in small pieces, and bake for 20 minutes (160°C) until pale brown. Allow to cool completely."},{"content":"When streusel has cooled, place white sesame seeds, black sesame seeds, cinnamon and honey in mixing bowl then heat <b>2 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add baked streusel pieces and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 1<b>. Return to prepared baking tray and bake for 15 minutes (160°C) until dry and golden brown. Leave to cool completely."},{"content":"When streusel has cooled, remove mousse rings from freezer, dust surface with cocoa powder, then remove metal rings (see tip). Place in the centre of serving plates and decorate the outsides with pieces of streusel before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Heat the outside of the ring gently to remove the mousse.","Leftover streusel can be stored in an airtight container or frozen for up to <b>1 month.<b>","It is normal for the streusel to melt and spread slightly during baking."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","3h","4 portions"]}